style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> an </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">International Relations and Politics </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">u</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ndergraduate at the University of Sheffield </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">partaking </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">in the Parliamentary Outreach Scheme</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> I am also the daughter of a small arable farmer in Herefordshire</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> which means that I have experienced first-hand the </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">impacts that governmental initiatives and policies have on British farmers. </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">I will restrict my focus around the challenges facing arable fa</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">rmers in the UK today</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> in order to obtain British food security.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:7pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The relationship between the price of food and the cost of producing it</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:5pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.41pt; padding-left:5.29pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> relationship between the price of f</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ood and the cost of production follow</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> a very simple economic rule of </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">causa</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">lity</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> where </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">a shift in </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">production costs </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">results in an increase in</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> consumer price</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">. However, </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">in recent years the rapid increase in production costs have left </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">British farmers</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> and consumers alike</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">helplessly exposed to the violent fluctuations </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">global prices. As </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">actors in </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">the </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">international </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">food market</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">, farmers have slowly accept</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> that the commodities they </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">consume</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> like</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> oil</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> and fertilisers</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> are</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> set </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">in accordance to</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> global prices</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">In an effort to subsist in the global market place, British farmers have been</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> forced</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">become internationally aware in order to</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> make calculated decisions on when whether to forward buy raw materials or </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">when to sell their produce at the highest </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">perceived </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">pri</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ce. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">The fact that the</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> HGCA publishes monthly Defra forecasts of cereal supply and d</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">emand for the UK </span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">covering</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> areas of availability, consumption, exports or stocks</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> around the world, evident</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ly sho</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">w</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> that British farming is more akin to calculated gambling.</span><span style="background-color:#fffdf0; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.41pt; padding-left:5.29pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">The UK </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">s a highly successful agricultural industry but i</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">n recent years, it </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">has been hard to ignore the </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">inflationary pressures</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> bearing heavily upon British consumers and producer alike. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">With the UK n</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">amed as one of the top countries with the </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">highest rates of food inflation in Europe</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">UK has seen food price inflation rise from 3</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">.1% in 2012 to stabilising around 4.4% in mid-2013. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.41pt; padding-left:5.29pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">British producers first experienced evident </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">nflationary </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">pressure in</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> 2008 when </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">world crude oil prices almost doubled in 12 months, driven by both strong global demand and extraction constraints. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">Fa</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">mers were first hit through</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> increased</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">r</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">ed </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">d</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">iesel </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">prices</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> which saw prices per litre rise </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">from 35p in 20</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">06 to its peak in 2013 at 73p. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">he doubling of red diesel prices over the last seven years has</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> had a serious effect on the production costs of </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">British far</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">mers</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:6.67pt; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:super">1</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 26.76pt; padding-left:5.44pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> impact of inflationary pressure</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> of higher </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">fuel prices has had a direct impact not only in the cost of running machinery but also in their use of </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">Agricultural</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> C</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">ontractors. </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">Contractors are employed to preform </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">contracting</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> has caused</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> producers to consider bearing the brunt of investing in their own machinery, a</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">the job</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> that farmers cannot physically do themselves or cannot afford to </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">purchase the</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt"> advanced</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAowAAAACCAYAAADSFo1XAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAA+SURBVFhH7daxDQBACAMxNs/o/NNSMIEjsYB1BVV/Sdox0IAGNKABDWhAAxrYDcyvaAQIECBAgAABAgROgQcelE8z3iDBtQAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==" width="651" height="1" alt="" style="margin-left:8.85pt; margin-top:10.9pt; position:absolute; z-index:0" /></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:9pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.8pt; padding-left:6.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:9pt">Boiler Juice, ‘</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">Price of Red Diesel’</span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Gisha; font-size:9pt">http://ww